    I heard about and used the 3M rust inhibitor about 3 years ago, $18
dollars a can was steep I thought. It was designed to be used in body shops
that did a lot of colision repair and needed to protect inner areas from
corrosion after replacement (thus the long tube). 3M also makes a weldable
rustihibitor primer. This is great for primming the inner parts of rockers
etc. before welding in.

ronnie

